<br>
Sure charm may break early, but that's why you'll choose less MR mobs and that's also why it should have -MR debuff on it.  You won't be able to keep a mob charmed constantly, but it really shouldn't be that way in the first place.  People complain about chanter charm, imagine if a much more survivable bard was given the ability to keep high level super hard hitting mobs charmed?  Everybody would call for nerfs, especially enchanters.<br>
<br>
The idea that no more than 2 mobs can attack a charmed pet is good for bards, but then only for bards.  If you changed charm such that it effected all charm, enchanters and necro's would go crazy.  But then again, it's a special change to coding, and you know how much of a chance that's going to happen (Also, now a days, damage from 2 mobs is going to be a lot more than a normal group of 6 PC's, so it'll be more like duo-trio kiting than swarm kiting, but still a problem.)<br>
<br>
The &quot;damage shield&quot; thing won't work though.  The whole point of swarmkiting is that the bard gains as little agro as possible.  You need to build quite a bit of agro for mobs to stop attacking your pet over you and since you're going to be pretty close to 0 agro on your swarm anyway, you'll still be able to swarm kite.  Song of Dawn is the easy solution for this.  If a swarm mob gets uppity, simply pulse it once and he'll be right back on your pet. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=espioidsavant>Espio Idsavant</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://lanys.evercrest.com/user-images/966/biggrinjester.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 109<br> <font color=#330000>(6/4/04 7:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19466.topic&index=11>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://lanys.evercrest.com/user-images/966/eqpa-espleave-mini2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sony's song thread</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Fortunately, we don't lose mana on missed notes, you won't ever fizzle 3 times and be out of mana<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Was this changed?  I quite clearly remember missing a note on desperate dirge and seeing my mana bar fall. <p><img src="http://lanys.evercrest.com/user-images/966/espiosig.jpg" align="left">
