<br>
The advantage to this is a bard with Time+ and 6k+ mana pool couldnt swarm any longer then a casual player with a 3k mana pool. I assume that a bard with 6k+ has better mana regen then a 3k bard so it will take them roughly the same ammount of time to med for another charm. (A long time.)<br>
<br>
To prevent abuse by loading up on FT while taking off mana gear (high FT with a small mana pool would reduce the time between OoM to FoM) set a minimum yet high mana cost per tick. So 150 mana or 5% mana per tick, which ever is greater.<br>
<br>
Set the maximum duration of charm (if the mob doesn't break early) to two minutes. (5% per tick for twenty ticks should use almost 100% of your mana), but permit charm break with the &quot;/pet get lost&quot; command so you can end the charm at any time to save what mana you have left.<br>
<br>
These changes would seem to require special code not in the game now. But these changes should prevent long term swarm kiting and put charm back into the &quot;emergency only&quot; catagory of crowd control. After all, would you use all your fade mana for two minutes of charm? You might, if conditions became dire enough.<br>
<br>
This isn't perfect. There could be ways to abuse it to swarm for a short burst of exp. But its just an idea I haven't seen posted before. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=425957"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:small;">I</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:x-small;">mpresario </span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:small;">F</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:x-small;">urioso </span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:small;">P</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:x-small;">resto</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
