<br>
Example #1: Someone is going to Hedge or TT in PoN. You take the normal route running off the gliff near gobbies looking up and all that. You land on the other side and are greated by a nice bard swarm that you had no real way of even seeing and can not go backwards on. Bard may or may not try and avoid you, but, heck, you're apt to be dropping in from overhead or coming around the corner of the wall there by the shade, and bam, there you are. MUNCH.<br>
<br>
Example #2: People are going to the CY's or castle in PoD. Bard keeps dragging a warm by the entrance to the bone wall. MUNCH<br>
<br>
Yeah, if you're up on toiler hill, people can see you from a mile. There are, however, places regularly swarmed where people can't see you until they are on top of you, and by that time there is a decent chance of them being dead.<br>
